Well, I'll help you
if we can find him.

771
00:32:31,183 --> 00:32:32,451
Look...

772
00:32:32,484 --> 00:32:33,986
don't worry, Chloe.

773
00:32:34,020 --> 00:32:35,554
Lucifer can take
care of himself.

774
00:32:35,587 --> 00:32:37,289
Found Lucifer's phone...

775
00:32:37,323 --> 00:32:39,058
in some bushes
on Alameda Street.

776
00:32:39,091 --> 00:32:40,726
Kidnappers must have
tossed it.

777
00:32:40,759 --> 00:32:41,627
What about, uh, traffic cams?

778
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,595
Maybe we can pull
a plate number.
No.

779
00:32:43,629 --> 00:32:46,132
I checked everything
within a mile radius. Nada.

780
00:32:46,165 --> 00:32:48,134
Must have grabbed him
in a blind spot.

781
00:32:48,167 --> 00:32:49,301
Unfortunately,

782
00:32:49,335 --> 00:32:51,470
I think we're dealing with
some pretty crafty bad guys.

783
00:32:51,503 --> 00:32:52,604
MAN:
I...

784
00:32:52,638 --> 00:32:54,240
can't... breathe!

785
00:32:54,273 --> 00:32:56,175
(groaning,
crying)

786
00:32:56,208 --> 00:32:59,078
Please don't crush him.
We've only just begun.

787
00:32:59,111 --> 00:33:01,780
No. Come on, man.
Ask us anything!

788
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,182
(cries)

789
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:04,683
All right.

790
00:33:04,716 --> 00:33:07,053
My face--
how did you do it?

791
00:33:07,086 --> 00:33:09,021
What?!
Well, the wings
are one thing,

792
00:33:09,055 --> 00:33:12,191
but my Devil face--
how did you take that?

793
00:33:12,224 --> 00:33:14,393
We've never seen
you before, man!

794
00:33:14,426 --> 00:33:15,761
Yeah, man.

795
00:33:15,794 --> 00:33:16,862
Never heard of you before today.

796
00:33:16,895 --> 00:33:20,499
I just got a name--
Daniel LaDoosh-- a pickup point,

797
00:33:20,532 --> 00:33:22,768
and that you got a thing
for gerbils.

798
00:33:22,801 --> 00:33:25,337
(crying)
I suppose you also deny
abducting Mr. Banales

799
00:33:25,371 --> 00:33:28,040
and leaving him to perish
in the desert, do you?

800
00:33:28,074 --> 00:33:30,042
He's the client
from last week, man!

801
00:33:30,076 --> 00:33:31,410
Right, man.

802
00:33:31,443 --> 00:33:33,145
His friend got him
the deluxe package.

803
00:33:33,179 --> 00:33:35,147
We did the
detail work here,

804
00:33:35,181 --> 00:33:36,415
and then our partner Sam
picked him up,

805
00:33:36,448 --> 00:33:38,284
took him to the spider hole
for a few hours,

806
00:33:38,317 --> 00:33:40,386
and dropped him
back off at the hotel.
Well, then,

807
00:33:40,419 --> 00:33:42,188
it seems
your colleague took a detour.

808
00:33:42,221 --> 00:33:43,555
Where does this Sam live?

809
00:33:43,589 --> 00:33:44,656
Koreatown!

810
00:33:44,690 --> 00:33:46,125
It's a pink building on Leeward.

811
00:33:46,158 --> 00:33:50,062
Apartment?
5B, man! 5B!

812
00:33:50,096 --> 00:33:52,398
Lovely. Thanks for your help.

813
00:33:52,431 --> 00:33:53,199
Hey, man!

814
00:33:53,232 --> 00:33:55,234
(crying)
Will you let
us go, man?

815
00:33:55,267 --> 00:33:57,369
(both scream)

816
00:33:57,403 --> 00:33:59,671
ELLA:
So, prints off the
key chain led to Josh.

817
00:33:59,705 --> 00:34:02,474
CHLOE:
Right. Tire treads
on the roadkill led to nothing.

818
00:34:02,508 --> 00:34:04,610
There's got to be
something we're missing.

819
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:06,145
Maybe Lancaster has something.

820
00:34:06,178 --> 00:34:07,613
We're screwed.

821
00:34:07,646 --> 00:34:09,181
Or not.

822
00:34:09,215 --> 00:34:10,782
Remember the detective
who found the key chain?

823
00:34:10,816 --> 00:34:13,252
He doesn't exist, at least
not at Lancaster PD.

824
00:34:13,285 --> 00:34:15,121
They only sent patrol
units to the scene.

825
00:34:15,154 --> 00:34:17,089
Whoa. You think
that was our guy?

826
00:34:17,123 --> 00:34:19,258
Killers often return to
the scene of the crime.

827
00:34:19,291 --> 00:34:19,958
DAN:
Which means

828
00:34:19,991 --> 00:34:21,227
he wasn't finding evidence.

829
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:22,528
He was trying to steal it.

830
00:34:22,561 --> 00:34:23,795
Should have known.

831
00:34:23,829 --> 00:34:25,397
Why should you have known?

832
00:34:25,431 --> 00:34:27,333
Lancaster doesn't know us,
we don't know them.

833
00:34:27,366 --> 00:34:29,101
Look, let's just look through
these photos, try and find him

834
00:34:29,135 --> 00:34:31,170
in the background, okay?
Yes, and then we
can nail his ass

835
00:34:31,203 --> 00:34:33,105
with facial
recognition software.

836
00:34:34,206 --> 00:34:35,707
Here he is.

837
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:37,643
But his back's to us.

838
00:34:37,676 --> 00:34:40,246
You guys... oh, my gosh.

839
00:34:40,279 --> 00:34:42,548
I knew... I knew
he didn't die in vain.

840
00:34:42,581 --> 00:34:44,750
What?
Who?

841
00:34:44,783 --> 00:34:47,153
Leo. See, look.

842
00:34:47,186 --> 00:34:49,621
There's our suspect,
right, leaving the scene,

843
00:34:49,655 --> 00:34:51,823
walking towards that van.

844
00:34:51,857 --> 00:34:54,260
Ryuk Road Crusher tires.

845
00:34:54,293 --> 00:34:55,361
Commercial grade.

846
00:34:55,394 --> 00:34:57,363
That's the van
that ran over Leo.

847
00:34:57,396 --> 00:34:59,231
I mean, this
pretty much confirms

848
00:34:59,265 --> 00:35:01,133
that this guy's
our killer.
CHLOE:
Okay.

849
00:35:01,167 --> 00:35:02,334
So maybe we can
get an ID.

850
00:35:02,368 --> 00:35:04,536
Let's run
the license plate.

851
00:35:09,541 --> 00:35:11,710
(knocking)

852
00:35:35,734 --> 00:35:37,203
Remember me?

853
00:35:42,241 --> 00:35:44,410
It's you.

854
00:35:44,443 --> 00:35:45,644
Yes.

855
00:35:45,677 --> 00:35:48,380
You know me as the Devil you so
rudely turned into an angel

856
00:35:48,414 --> 00:35:49,715
and then dumped
in the middle of the desert,

857
00:35:49,748 --> 00:35:51,650
but I don't know you,
so, come on,

858
00:35:51,683 --> 00:35:52,951
introduce yourself.

859
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:54,453
I'm Sam.
Yes, yes,

860
00:35:54,486 --> 00:35:56,222
I know that, but what are you?

861
00:35:56,255 --> 00:35:58,257
And how did my Father
get his hooks into you?

862
00:35:58,290 --> 00:35:59,358
Your father?

863
00:35:59,391 --> 00:36:01,260
Oh, come on,
don't be coy.

864
00:36:01,293 --> 00:36:02,594
Let me see.

865
00:36:02,628 --> 00:36:05,197
Unless Dad got jiggy
with some celestial babe

866
00:36:05,231 --> 00:36:07,333
after Mum, then
you're not my sibling,

867
00:36:07,366 --> 00:36:09,568
so... demon. Hmm?

868
00:36:09,601 --> 00:36:10,502
Changeling?

869
00:36:10,536 --> 00:36:13,672
I work for
an extreme kidnapping company.

870
00:36:13,705 --> 00:36:14,540
Snatched.

871
00:36:14,573 --> 00:36:16,308
Oh, do you now?
Well, do you know what?

872
00:36:16,342 --> 00:36:17,576
It doesn't matter
what you are because...

873
00:36:17,609 --> 00:36:19,278
this should take care of you.

874
00:36:19,311 --> 00:36:20,379
Whoa! Whoa!

875
00:36:20,412 --> 00:36:22,214
Whoa! I-- I'm sorry.

876
00:36:22,248 --> 00:36:24,650
I'm sorry I left you
in the desert.

877
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:26,452
I really am.

878
00:36:26,485 --> 00:36:28,854
And I'm sorry I left
that Steve guy there, too.

879
00:36:28,887 --> 00:36:30,556
I-- He was just a routine gig.

880
00:36:30,589 --> 00:36:31,790
I was gonna swap him for you,

881
00:36:31,823 --> 00:36:33,692
but when I went to
pull you out of the van,

882
00:36:33,725 --> 00:36:37,963
you... you had
friggin' wings, man!

883
00:36:37,996 --> 00:36:39,965
Well, duh!
Wings that you put there

884
00:36:39,998 --> 00:36:41,367
at the behest of my Father!

885
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:43,369
Now stop lying!
I'm not!

886
00:36:43,402 --> 00:36:45,637
I didn't mean to hurt anyone.

887
00:36:45,671 --> 00:36:46,538
I swear.

888
00:36:46,572 --> 00:36:48,440
And believe me,
I didn't want to run,

889
00:36:48,474 --> 00:36:50,242
but you scared
the hell out of me.

890
00:36:50,276 --> 00:36:51,343
Right, you listen, Sammy,

891
00:36:51,377 --> 00:36:52,878
I know you're
just the messenger,

892
00:36:52,911 --> 00:36:55,814
so why don't you deliver
a message on my behalf?

893
00:36:57,383 --> 00:37:01,653
I define who I am, not Him.

894
00:37:01,687 --> 00:37:02,821
Me!

895
00:37:02,854 --> 00:37:04,723
(cries)

896
00:37:04,756 --> 00:37:08,327
Oh, bloody hell.

897
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:10,396
They're back, aren't they?

898
00:37:10,429 --> 00:37:11,897
How?
(whoosh)

899
00:37:11,930 --> 00:37:13,432
How are you doing this?

900
00:37:13,465 --> 00:37:15,434
Did my Father
give you some kind of totem?

901
00:37:15,467 --> 00:37:16,602
A talisman?

902
00:37:16,635 --> 00:37:18,437
What?
I'm telling you, I don't...

903
00:37:18,470 --> 00:37:20,572
I don't know what's happening.

904
00:37:20,606 --> 00:37:22,541
And I don't know your dad.

905
00:37:22,574 --> 00:37:26,545
Unless, is your,
is your dad the Sinnerman?

906
00:37:28,447 --> 00:37:30,949
Quite the opposite.
Who's the Sinnerman?

907
00:37:30,982 --> 00:37:31,950
That's, that's who,

908
00:37:31,983 --> 00:37:33,819
who hired me to kidnap you.

909
00:37:33,852 --> 00:37:37,389
He's, he's, he's a scary dude.

910
00:37:37,423 --> 00:37:39,825
Huge crime boss.
I owed him big time.

911
00:37:39,858 --> 00:37:41,793
But because I didn't
finish the job,

912
00:37:41,827 --> 00:37:42,994
I'm as good as dead now.

913
00:37:43,028 --> 00:37:44,396
That's why I was running.

914
00:37:44,430 --> 00:37:46,365
And where do I find
this Sinnerman?

915
00:37:46,398 --> 00:37:47,766
You don't.

916
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:49,301
He finds you.

917
00:37:49,335 --> 00:37:50,502
CHLOE:
Lucifer?

918
00:37:53,405 --> 00:37:54,740
Get up.

919
00:37:54,773 --> 00:37:55,841
Up.

920
00:37:55,874 --> 00:37:58,510
Come on, get up.

921
00:37:58,544 --> 00:38:00,712
Put your hands
behind your back.

922
00:38:03,114 --> 00:38:05,317
What happened to you?
I...

923
00:38:07,853 --> 00:38:09,621
I don't know.

924
00:38:20,866 --> 00:38:23,001
Decker, it ain't good.

925
00:38:23,034 --> 00:38:25,404
Lieutenant, look, I-I know
what you're gonna say.

926
00:38:25,437 --> 00:38:26,805
And, even though
we caught our guy,

927
00:38:26,838 --> 00:38:29,941
Lucifer was way out of line,
and I-I don't disagree,

928
00:38:29,975 --> 00:38:31,543
but here's what
you got to know

929
00:38:31,577 --> 00:38:33,345
about our unorthodox methods...

930
00:38:33,379 --> 00:38:34,713
Detective, you...
I am Lucifer's partner,

931
00:38:34,746 --> 00:38:37,983
yes, you're right,
but you know what?

932
00:38:38,016 --> 00:38:39,551
He's mine, too.

933
00:38:39,585 --> 00:38:42,688
And, for whatever reason,
we make an effective team.

934
00:38:42,721 --> 00:38:46,458
And will be even more so
when I stop investing

935
00:38:46,492 --> 00:38:50,061
on a, um... personal level.

936
00:38:50,095 --> 00:38:51,963
I am here to solve crimes.

937
00:38:51,997 --> 00:38:54,566
Not to see his... his thing

938
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,402
or whatever, which is...

939
00:38:56,435 --> 00:38:59,971
not something
that you need to know.

940
00:39:00,005 --> 00:39:01,206
Right. Look, point is,

941
00:39:01,239 --> 00:39:04,643
you can say what you want,
but I know I'm a good detective

942
00:39:04,676 --> 00:39:07,045
and I have a damn good
solve rate to prove that.

943
00:39:07,078 --> 00:39:08,780
Okay.

944
00:39:10,882 --> 00:39:11,917
Okay.

945
00:39:11,950 --> 00:39:13,419
Okay.

946
00:39:13,452 --> 00:39:15,554
I just came down here

947
00:39:15,587 --> 00:39:17,956
to let you know that your perp
has been released on bail.

948
00:39:17,989 --> 00:39:19,124
Oh.

949
00:39:19,157 --> 00:39:20,992
W-Wait, how is that possible?

950
00:39:21,026 --> 00:39:22,027
Don't know.

951
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:23,429
Friends in high places, I guess.

952
00:39:23,462 --> 00:39:24,596
But there's got to be something.

953
00:39:24,630 --> 00:39:26,465
I mean, don't-don't you care?

954
00:39:26,498 --> 00:39:27,966
You do what you can, Decker.

955
00:39:27,999 --> 00:39:29,635
You can't save them all.

956
00:39:29,668 --> 00:39:31,002
Oh.

957
00:39:31,036 --> 00:39:34,406
But, um, good luck
with Lucifer's... thing

958
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:35,874
or whatever.

959
00:39:53,525 --> 00:39:55,461
(elevator bell dings)

960
00:39:59,531 --> 00:40:02,601
Oh, hello, Brother.

961
00:40:02,634 --> 00:40:04,603
So, did Remedy cure
what ails you?

962
00:40:04,636 --> 00:40:06,171
Did her massage
make anything

963
00:40:06,204 --> 00:40:07,038
pop out?

964
00:40:07,072 --> 00:40:08,674
Talking about your wings,
of course.

965
00:40:08,707 --> 00:40:12,578
No, mine are still absent.

966
00:40:12,611 --> 00:40:14,480
But yours, on the other hand...

967
00:40:16,682 --> 00:40:19,184
(softly):
Oh.

968
00:40:19,217 --> 00:40:20,586
Lucifer, I'm not angry with you

969
00:40:20,619 --> 00:40:22,721
that you somehow
got your wings back,

970
00:40:22,754 --> 00:40:24,456
or even that you
cut them off again,

971
00:40:24,490 --> 00:40:28,193
as foul as that may be.

972
00:40:28,226 --> 00:40:30,529
I'm angry with myself.

973
00:40:31,530 --> 00:40:33,599
Because somehow I made you feel

974
00:40:33,632 --> 00:40:35,634
like you couldn't confide in me.

975
00:40:35,667 --> 00:40:38,770
Well, comparing body parts
is never good for the male ego,

976
00:40:38,804 --> 00:40:40,672
especially between brothers.

977
00:40:40,706 --> 00:40:43,742
But that's just it, Luci.

978
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:47,145
My ego should never be an issue.

979
00:40:47,178 --> 00:40:50,215
I am an angel.

980
00:40:50,248 --> 00:40:51,583
A soldier of God.

981
00:40:51,617 --> 00:40:53,885
His favorite son.

982
00:40:53,919 --> 00:40:56,054
Oh, that's gonna be a thing,
isn't it?

983
00:40:56,087 --> 00:40:59,124
(stifled laugh)

984
00:40:59,157 --> 00:41:02,127
Listen, Father, He...

985
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:04,763
works in mysterious ways.

986
00:41:04,796 --> 00:41:07,766
I was tested once and I failed.

987
00:41:07,799 --> 00:41:09,801
I'm not gonna fail again.

988
00:41:09,835 --> 00:41:12,070
Because this time, I have faith.

989
00:41:12,103 --> 00:41:15,674
Excellent.

990
00:41:15,707 --> 00:41:18,243
And I suppose
this won't bother you.

991
00:41:18,276 --> 00:41:20,746
(whoosh)

992
00:41:23,715 --> 00:41:25,984
But you...

993
00:41:26,017 --> 00:41:27,218
you cut them off.

994
00:41:27,252 --> 00:41:30,556
I did, but the pesky things
seem to be a bit more tenacious

995
00:41:30,589 --> 00:41:32,624
this time around.

996
00:41:32,658 --> 00:41:34,960
Well, like I said, I have faith.

997
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:37,295
I'm sure it's all
a part of God's plan.

998
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:38,296
(laughing):
Yes!

999
00:41:38,329 --> 00:41:40,599
If you mean his plan
to continually manipulate

1000
00:41:40,632 --> 00:41:42,701
and control me, then agreed.

1001
00:41:42,734 --> 00:41:44,603
Because, by the way,

1002
00:41:44,636 --> 00:41:46,905
he didn't just
give my wings back,

1003
00:41:46,938 --> 00:41:48,907
he took my Devil face as well.

1004
00:41:50,842 --> 00:41:53,078
Luci, do you realize
what this means?

1005
00:41:53,111 --> 00:41:56,214
Perhaps Father is trying
to show you that,

1006
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:57,549
that you've been forgiven.

1007
00:41:57,583 --> 00:41:59,885
What if I don't want
His forgiveness?

1008
00:41:59,918 --> 00:42:03,622
But, Brother,
if you can be redeemed,

1009
00:42:03,655 --> 00:42:05,090
that means that anyone can.

1010
00:42:06,758 --> 00:42:09,561
Now, isn't that divine?

1011
00:42:09,595 --> 00:42:12,097
(scoffs)

1012
00:42:12,130 --> 00:42:16,034
I'm not sure that
this is divinity at work here.

1013
00:42:16,067 --> 00:42:19,605
(sighs)

1014
00:42:19,638 --> 00:42:23,675
Have you ever heard
of someone named the Sinnerman?

1015
00:42:24,776 --> 00:42:26,177
The Sinnerman?

1016
00:42:29,715 --> 00:42:31,216
No.

1017
00:42:31,249 --> 00:42:33,685
Why?

1018
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:37,656
That's who kidnapped me.

1019
00:42:48,634 --> 00:42:49,635
At first, I thought it was a...

1020
00:42:49,668 --> 00:42:51,336
an emissary on Earth

1021
00:42:51,369 --> 00:42:53,304
working on Dad's behalf, but
then, the more I think about it,

1022
00:42:53,338 --> 00:42:55,306
the more I think...

1023
00:42:55,340 --> 00:42:59,577
maybe this isn't our Father
who art in Heaven at all.

1024
00:43:05,651 --> 00:43:06,618
But something much,

1025
00:43:06,652 --> 00:43:09,988
much darker.

